= TuringArena - Create algorithmic challenges

TuringArena is a toolkit to define challenges which require an algorithmic solution,
and to automatically test the code of solutions.

For the documentation see http://www.turingarena.org[the TuringArena website].

== Getting started with Docker

[source,bash]
  # evaluate an example problem
  $ sudo docker run -i --rm turingarena/turingarena evaluate -p sum_of_two_numbers < solution.cpp
  $ sudo docker run -i --rm turingarena/turingarena evaluate -p sum_of_two_numbers -x python < solution.py

[source,bash]
  # run your own problem (in a sub-directory of the working directory)
  $ sudo docker run -i --rm -v $PWD:/problems:ro turingarena/turingarena evaluate -p problem_name < solution.cpp

[source,bash]
  # one-line examples
  $ echo 'int sum(int a,int b){return a+b;}' | sudo docker run -i --rm turingarena/turingarena evaluate -p sum_of_two_numbers
  $ echo 'def sum(a,b): return a+b' | sudo docker run -i --rm turingarena/turingarena evaluate -p sum_of_two_numbers -x python
